reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 28, 2023
reviews.reviewText: This is a great shoe rack. Exceeds my expectations, easy to assemble, light-weighted, sturdy and stable, fits well, very compact and the same time has plenty of space to store multiple shoes. I am fully satisfied with my purchase. Perfect combination of quality and price. Thank you.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 3, 2024
reviews.reviewText: 1st of all had all parts! It was easy to put together if you take time and follow directions, just took a little time. For the price it's worth it. Exactly what I needed.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 16, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Great organizer for the price
reviews.reviewText: Pros: • Fast shipping • Great quality for price • Under $40 • Sturdy • Save me floor space in my room • Easy to see my shoes • Room for coats, scarfs, hats and bags • Elevates room •••• Cons: • Have to put it together • Wish there was more flat shelf pieces

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 23, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Not the most sturdy, but plenty of room for all my shoes! Directions were pretty clear, but I hardly used them. Putting it together was pretty easy.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 31, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Perfect for tight spaces! (and fits mens size 13 sneakers!)
reviews.reviewText: We do not have a mudroom or a dedicated space for shoes, etc. We come in thru our basement and we always just had a pile-mountain-of shoes! I was skeptical of this as I know these things can be cheaply made, etc. This was easy to put together ( i did stand on my stairs to push the rods in to make sure they were 100% in place) and it holds so many pairs of shoes! Bonus-my husband is a size 13 and it fits his shoes!!! So far so good!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 19, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Perfect for what we needed!
reviews.reviewText: We had been accumulating too many shoes on our old shoe rack and I liked this one best because it had spots for boots and hooks on the sides. And it holds everything perfectly! Makes the space look so much nicer!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 16, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Such a space saver!
reviews.reviewText: I love this! I had a nice wicker basket for my kids shoes but they were so unorganized and for the same reason they would use the same shoes every day and after a couple of months I had to throw out new pairs because they had outgrown them. With this rack, the shoes are organized and visible.It’s also very easy to instal and you can opt to add as many shelves as you’d like. I got the 10 shelf rack but only used 7 shelves.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 27, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Great at first, then it wasn’t
reviews.reviewText: So this review is after having this item since the beginning of February it will November next week. Putting this together was tedious but not difficult at all, there is a lot of small bars that they give you the cutest little mallet to make sure it’s tightly secure into place. This shoe rack was pretty sturdy no issues the first 6-7 months but since august pieces keep pushing out and have to be put back in and falling out as well. So many of the pieces have bent that they don’t stay in or hold any weight that those shoe cubbies are useless. Last night the entire shoe rack fell down with all the shoes and items on it, and I will not be putting it back together. Period. It really was such a good idea and it looked so neat and sturdy, I do have children that use the shoe rack as well so with that being said this purchase may be better suited for homes without kiddos lol I say that only because my eleven year old with just kinda shove her shoes in her cubbies and that is were the bars originally started popping out and went bad from there.

I like it alot but the only thing I wish it had one that had higher shelfs for hi heels . As alot of hi heels are too tall too fit nicely in the sheles. It's great for shoes that are hi heels 👠. But I do like it
Bought a knockoff and all the rods bent day 2. This one is way more sturdy. Only holds about two pairs of shoes per shelf but can hold a bunch of sandals per shelf. Really tall, and really sturdy.
The media could not be loaded. Easy to assemble, manual was very helpful too and I really love that it has good quality, very study and can creatively fit into whatever space that you have.
